<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 21 at 4:23AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A band of snow will move through the western half of North
Central MT through 530 AM MDT...
At 420 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of snow about 17
miles west of Cascade, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Snow, with poor visibility.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect some roadways to become snow covered and slippery as
this band of snow moves through.
Some Locations impacted include... Great Falls, Choteau, Cascade,
Lincoln, Fairfield, Augusta, Ulm, and Simms.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 15 between mile markers 237 and 327.
Highway 200 between mile markers 66 and 139.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
